Gombe State Governor, Alhaji Muhammadu Inuwa Yahaya has ordered the immediate suspension of the Chairman and Members of the Gombe State Board of Internal Revenue ( BOIR). Consequently, the Chairman, Salisu Adamu Dukku has been directed to hand over the Affairs of the Board to Abubakar Inuwa Tata, Chairman, Fiscal Responsibility Commission who will take charge as administrator pending further action. ALSO READ: Insecurity: Yoruba group to Buha­ri, call Miyetti Allah to order Why Gombe Christians missed 2019 pilgrimage ― Gombe gov Discovery of oil will not divide us, Bauchi gov assures… Severe acute malnutrition: CISLAC charges Gombe legislators… Gombe begins vaccination of over one million cattle, sheep,… Equally, according to a statement by Ismaila Uba Misilli, Senior Special Assistant on Media to the Governor,  the chairman and the following members; Abubakar Magaji Difa, Ismail Ishaq and Umar Shamaki Tula are to report to the Office of the Secretary to the State Government for further instructions. In the same vein, the following Senior Management staff have been directed to hand over to their immediate subordinates and report to the Office of the Head of Service for further Instructions. They are Sadiq Abubakar Mohammed – Head of Department,  Collection Sulaiman Adamu- Head of Department,  Internal Control and Mohammed Usman Bello- State Motor Registrar. No reason was given for the suspension of the officers but an impeccable source said that the Governor has not been happy with the poor internally generated revenue in the recent time. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE.